<p>
    <h2>A* Pathfinding and State Machines</h2>
    <br />For this project, I began implementing an A* pathfinding algorithm, like the one used in my
    <a href="https://zakstanyer.wixsite.com/zakstanyer/tankshootout" target="_blank" style="text-decoration: underline; padding: 2px"> Tank Shootout</a> game. This worked well initially, 
    but as you progress to later rounds of the game and more enemies are on screen and the area gets expanded, it became ineffective having every enemy trying to pathfind and it affected the game's performance.
    So in the end I have used a NavMesh for simple movement of the enemies, and then I implemented state machines to give the enemies complex behaviour. I found that this solution was less intensive on my system.
</p>

